  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Is spot counselling for reserved candidates?",
  "response": "Spot counselling is a process that allows eligible candidates to secure admission to educational institutions or programs after the official counseling sessions have concluded, typically when there are leftover seats. Whether spot counselling is available for reserved candidates (such as those belonging to SC/ST/OBC categories, EWS, or other reserved groups) depends on the specific rules and regulations set by the conducting authority or the institution in question.\n\nHere are some general points to consider:\n\n1. **Reservation Policies:** Most educational institutions and government bodies have reservation policies in place to ensure representation of various reserved categories. These policies often include specific quotas for each reserved category during both regular and spot counselling sessions.\n\n2. **Eligibility:** Reserved candidates who did not secure a seat during the regular counseling rounds are usually eligible to participate in spot counselling. However, their eligibility might depend on the availability of reserved category seats and the specific criteria set by the conducting authority.\n\n3. **Priority Allocation:** In some cases, reserved category seats might be allocated priority during spot counselling to ensure that reserved candidates have an opportunity to secure admission. This can vary based on the institution's policies.\n\n4. **Documentation:** Reserved candidates may need to provide appropriate documentation to prove their eligibility for reservation benefits during spot counselling. Ensure that all necessary certificates and documents are up-to-date and readily available.\n\n5. **Check Official Guidelines:** It's crucial to refer to the official guidelines issued by the respective counseling authority or institution. Policies can vary significantly between different educational boards, universities, and regions.\n\n6. **Deadlines and Procedures:** Spot counselling usually operates on a first-come, first-served basis for the remaining seats. Make sure to adhere to the deadlines and follow the procedures outlined by the conducting body to maximize your chances of securing a seat.\n\n**Recommendation:**\n\nTo get precise information tailored to your situation, consider the following steps:\n\n- **Visit the Official Website:** Check the official website of the counseling authority or the institution you're interested in for detailed information about spot counselling procedures and eligibility criteria for reserved candidates.\n\n- **Contact Support Services:** Reach out to the support or helpline services provided by the counseling body or institution for personalized assistance.\n\n- **Stay Updated:** Keep an eye on official announcements and updates, as policies and procedures can change based on institutional decisions or regulatory guidelines.\n\nBy following these steps, you can ensure that you have the most accurate and relevant information regarding spot counselling opportunities for reserved candidates.",
